result.notes:
Plankton analysis data from a survey carried out in the Irish Sea between 19th 
April to 11th May 1994. Aims of the surveys included,


-   To survey plankton populations and hydrographic structure from the Malin 
    Shelf to the North Channel for evidence of transport of copepods into the 
    Irish Sea.
-   To sample fish eggs and larvae.

This data consists of the numbers of ichthyoplankton and zooplankton collected 
by high speed towed net (HSTN), both coarse and fine mesh, and by Longhurst 
Hardy Plankton Recorder (LHPR), plus associated positional data and volumes 
filtered.
